iSummaryContaineruniface_104ppt1665702803071.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ppt1665702803071.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ppt1665702803071.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ppt1665702803071\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                                 \n New Component\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Create a new component signature.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ppt1665702803071__p_d6095e1_d6096e1_d6097e1\">The implementation can be for a Uniface component or an operating system component, but not both, and any number of foreign components.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ppt1665702803071__section_w4z_x2f_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1218874e58\">Fields</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ppt1665702803071__ul_yzk_y2f_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ppt1665702803071__li_d3062e1_d3063e1_d3064e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jrq1665702585385.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jrq1665702585385.html\" title=\"Name of the development object, which uniquely identifies it.\">Name</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ppt1665702803071__li_d3065e1_d3066e1_d3067e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xrw1665702585620.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrw1665702585620.html\" title=\"Use this property to briefly describe the development object in up to 256 Unicode characters.\">Description</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ppt1665702803071__li_d3068e1_d3069e1_d3070e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vju1665702803227.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vju1665702803227.html\" title=\"Defines a component interface with no component implementation. The interface is internally visible to Uniface but without an implementation, it cannot be used.\">None</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ppt1665702803071__li_d3071e1_d3072e1_d3073e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yuu1665702803295.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yuu1665702803295.html\" title=\"Implementations for the new component.\">Implementation in</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ppt1665702803071__section_wtr_z2f_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1218874e103\">How to</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ppt1665702803071__ul_l3c_1ff_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ppt1665702803071__li_d3074e1_d3075e1_d3076e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zzx1665702678830.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzx1665702678830.html\" title=\"Use the Signature Editor to create or modify component signatures. Signatures of Uniface components are automatically generated during compilation. Signatures of non-Uniface components can be created or imported.\">Define a Component Signature</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kqj1665702890051.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Component Implementations</a><p>The component signature specifies the implementation a component, which determines the technology used to deploy it, such as Uniface, C, or Java.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8421795\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8421795\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "New Component Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 New Component Create a new component signature. The implementation can be for a Uniface component or an operating system component, but not both, and any number of foreign components. Fields Name Description None Implementation in How to Define a Component Signature Related Links Component Implementations The component signature specifies the implementation a component, which determines the technology used to deploy it, such as Uniface, C, or Java. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}